				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7881563#post-4291434</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7881563/scp-4249#post-4291434</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 26 Jun 2019 03:52:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gabriel McQueen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4558836</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Some of Mr. de Santos' word choices feel to me to be unnecessarily obtuse. Sofas, and simple names for them (sofa, settee, couch, etc.) had existed in a form we would recognize in the modern day by, conservatively, over a hundred years prior to the 1850's. Referring to it as some kind of &quot;cushioned bench&quot; or &quot;padded seat&quot; made me wonder for a moment if this was an explorer from an alternate universe, quite similar to our own, but where couches for some narrative reason hadn't been invented. Similarly, it seems wild to me to see a fabric bag and refer to it as a &quot;clump&quot; or &quot;amalgam&quot; rather than, say, a bag or sack.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
